cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing user-generated music listening events and investigating the performance of a collaborative filtering recommender. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper analyzes music genre preferences for homogeneity within more fine-grained age groups and with respect to gender and countries. 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing music listening events and preferences. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is a possible category as the paper focuses on the online music listening culture of kids and adolescents. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper investigates the performance of a recommender system tailored to different age groups.
